[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> fov = 900.0
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> # At the first boundary, the parity changes
[?2004l[?2004h> # (floor(X*freq + xoff) + floor(Z*freq + zoff) + inv) & 1 changes
[?2004l[?2004h> # Z = d * fov / (y - 900)
[?2004l[?2004h> # X = (x - 1200) * d / (y - 900)
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> # At the boundary x for a given y, we have:
[?2004l[?2004h> # Let ix = floor(X*freq + xoff), iz = floor(Z*freq + zoff)
[?2004l[?2004h> # The parity changes when X*freq + xoff crosses an integer boundary
[?2004l[?2004h> # OR Z*freq + zoff crosses an integer boundary
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> # But we can't determine which one changes. Let's try a different approach:
[?2004l[?2004h> # Instead of trying to match the exact formula, let's just use a simpler
[?2004l[?2004h> # formula that produces the same visual pattern
[?2004l[?2004h> 
