[?2004l[?2004h> # Now let's determine d and freq by solving for the first boundary position
[?2004l[?2004h> # At the first boundary, the parity changes.
[?2004l[?2004h> # The parity is (floor(X*freq + xoff) + floor(Z*freq + zoff) + inv) & 1
[?2004l[?2004h> # At the boundary, either X*freq + xoff or Z*freq + zoff crosses an integer.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
